{"word":"προσεῖδον","slug":"προσεῖδον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>προσεῖδον</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>-ῐδεῖν</el>) (<a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>-ῐδών</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>aor2 without any <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> in use, <a href='S:προσοράω'><el>προσοράω</el></a> being used instead.\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to look at</i> or <i>upon</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—also in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <el>προσῐδέσθαι</el>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <el>προσείδομαι</el>, <i>to be like</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}